					<head>Prophets</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/n79054379  lccn.loc.gov/n80008477" rend="visible">
						<summary>Former Prophets, accentuated and punctuated, with masorah magna and parva.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he">Hebrew</textLang>
						<msItem n="0" rend="" class="lccn.loc.gov/n80008477">
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Nevi᾿im </title>
							<title xml:lang="he">נביאים</title>
							<locus from="1v" to="206v"/>
							<colophon xml:lang="he">נבצע בשנת <date when="1461" calendar="Seleucid">אתש[ע"ב] לשטרות</date> יהא סימ[ ] ברב <name type="person" role="patron">זכריה רי"ת הידוע אלבוני</name> אלה' יזכיה[ ]ניו ולה[ב] מעתה ועד עולם הוא וזרעו וזרע זרעו אנס"ו ויתקיים עליו מקרא שכ[ ] ה' וישמ' יאר ה' פניו אל' ישא ה' פניו אל' וג' ספרא חלשא ומ[ס]ינא קל ה[ק ] <name type="person" role="scribe">בניה בן סעדיה בן זכריה בן מרגז</name> אלה ימחול לי על מה ששגיתי וטעית[ ] ונסתר מ[ ] שגיאות מי יבין מנסתרות נקיני אנ"ס ישע יקרב ששון יע[ר]<locus n="206v"/>
							</colophon>
							<msItem rend="v">
								<locus from="1v" to="32v"/>
								<title xml:lang="en">Joshua</title>
							</msItem>
							<msItem rend="v">
								<title xml:lang="en">Judges</title>
								<locus from="32v" to="62r"/>
							</msItem>
							<msItem rend="v">
								<title xml:lang="en">Samuel</title>
								<locus from="62r" to="132v"/>
								<note>
									<p>2Samuel starts at folio <locus n="100v"/>.</p>
								</note>
							</msItem>
							<msItem rend="v">
								<title xml:lang="en">Kings</title>
								<locus from="132v" to="206v"/>
								<note>
									<p>2Kings starts at folio <locus n="171r"/>.</p>
								</note>
							</msItem>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex of the 15th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
								<support>Paper codex. </support>
								<extent>206 folios<dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>283</height>
										<width>205</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>205</height>
										<width>126</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>206 folios (+ 2 modern paper flyleaves at the beginning and at the end). </p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>21 quires of 10 leaves each, apart from the first and the last quire, which have only 8 leaves each. </p>
									<p>The quires are signed with Hebrew letters on the first page and marked with catchwords on the last page.  </p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>The first three leaves and the last leaf are not fully preserved. </p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1" ruledLines="19" writtenLines="19">
									<p>Masorah magna occupies generally one line at the top and one line in the bottom margin of the page. </p>
									<p>A number of masoretic rubrics is given at the end of each books. </p>
									<p>The titles of the books are written at the top of every page and the chapters are numbered with Hebrew letters by later hands. </p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="1">
							<summary>Oriental square script, punctuated, of  the 15th century. <name type="person" role="scribe">Benayah ben Se'adyah ben Zekharyah ben Margaz</name>: inscribed with his name in the colophon, folio 206v. For manuscripts of the same scribe see Or 2210, 2211, 2348, 2375 (<ref target="Margoliouth_1965" type="number">128</ref>, <ref target="Margoliouth_1965" type="number">138</ref>, <ref target="Margoliouth_1965" type="number">89</ref>, <ref target="Margoliouth_1965" type="number">147</ref>.</summary>
